[SN]TITLE[SN]
South African engineers go on strike

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Engineering and metal workers in South Africa have gone on strike after talks on Monday failed to reach an agreement over pay.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
1 July 2014 Last updated at 16:43 BST
The country's largest union, the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa), claims that more than 200,000 members are striking.
